reviews.text:
Absolutely delicious. I just needed some quick food for lunch and found this place. The food was really good. Staff was super friendly and they got the food to me so quickly. I'm very happy with my experience here.

edit to review. I have really liked going to this place for some time, but my experience yesterday really turned me away from the place. I went in though the drive though, normally it takes only a few minutes, this time I spent close to 25-30 minutes there. when I ordered the person seemed really snappy, though that may have just been my perception of it. finally when i got my food, absolutely everything was wrong with it, i got lime chicken with Spanish rice and balsamic vinaigrette, the only thing they got right in it was the chicken which was insanely dry compared to previous times.
I was on my work lunch and by the time i noticed they gave me everything wrong I had no time to go back and correct it. for the time waiting, the food gotten and the snappy server, i felt really disappointed in a place I have really loved so far. IDK if they have recently hired a lot of new people recently, but i think there needs to be some additional training or at least a double check the order.

I have I have literally coming it Bajio for the last 20 years. I remember when they were over in the bagel den area of river woods and when they used to have locations all over.

It is my favorite Mexican restaurant on earth. Their sweet rice is to die for. The burritos are exquisite, and you definitely have to give their shrimp tacos a try. At Bajio, everyone knows your name. Although Francisco and Raymond don‚Äôt work there anymore (they are missed), it is the best food ever. Would absolutely recommend.

Excellent Chicken Green Chile! I haven't been here since the one in Layton closed.  THIS PLACE IS THE BOMB! Sweet Rice, Anything with the Green Chile and the beans are awesome!  I definitely will always come here when in area.  I hope the locals know what a treasure they have!  Great and Friendly service as well today!

The past few times I‚Äôve been, they‚Äôve been incredibly stingy with their serving of meat. That all came to a head today when they put no meat whatsoever on my quesadilla. After so many negative visits and second chances, this was enough for me to not want to come back again. It‚Äôs really a shame because I used to love to stop by this place after work for dinner.
Good place to grab a quick bite. Comparable to several places in Utah county, but so good! I recommend these over the others. Good service.
